Head of Special Operations at the Independent Corrupt Practices and other Related Offences Commission (ICPC), Mr. Bako Nathan, has said the commission had blocked unspent funds of government agencies totaling N189 billion in 2019 and 2020. Nathan spoke yesterday in Abuja when he appeared before the House of Representatives Ad Hoc Committee investigating alleged corruption and abuse of nominal rolls and other corrupt practices by government agencies. He said the ICPC had been investigating allegations of corrupt practices in various government agencies over the years. The spokesman said ICPC blocked billions of naira in various government agencies which were allegedly dubiously spent and kept to shortchange the government.   Davido disburses N250m to 292 orphanages in 27 States     2023: ‘Campaigns of calumny won’t stop Atiku’      Gen. forfeits N10.9b properties to govt   - Advertisement - The House summoned the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), Mr. Boss Mustapha, and Minister of Finance, Budget and National Planning, Hajiya Zainab Ahmed, as well as heads of key government agencies over the alleged abuse and inflation of nominal rolls. - Advertisement - Committee Chairman Dachung Bagos said the committee would write to all the agencies that did not attend the sitting. He added that any agency that failed to attend would be treated as one of those abusing laid down rules and bloating their nominal rolls to defraud the government. Others summoned by the committee included the Head of the Service of the Federation, Accountant General of the Federation, the Auditor General of the Federation, and ICPC Chairman. The Chief Executive Officer of Federal Character Commission (FCC) and the Officer in Charge of IPPIS were also summoned. SPONSORED